node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. node.text: DuPont State Recreational Forest in North Carolina is home to some of the most thrilling mountain bike trails. There are 80 miles of trails across 11,000 acres. Here, biking isn't just a sport. It's a way of life. CNN's @CoyWire joins the pack from @redwolftours for a perfect day on the mountain.

node.title: 'The skinniest, bumpiest, wildest ride I've been on in my life'

node.text:
Face masks are now required inside all National Park Service buildings and in crowded outdoor locations, like busy trails and overlooks. This applies to everyone regardless of your vaccination status or the transmission levels within the community.⁠
⁠
(📸: Apu Gomes/AFP/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, footwear and text that says 'Pete Buttigieg and his husband Chasten have become parents CNN'.

node.text:
Pete Buttigieg and his husband Chasten have become first-time parents, the transportation secretary announced on Tuesday. "The process isn't done yet and we're thankful for the love, support, and respect for our privacy that has been offered to us. We can't wait to share more soon," said Buttigieg, the first out LGBTQ Cabinet secretary confirmed by the Senate.⁠
⁠
(📸: Joe Raedle/Getty Images)

node.text: Around 1.2 million people, including 540,000 children, have been impacted by the 7.2-magnitude earthquake which struck southwestern Haiti on Saturday morning, according to UNICEF. Tropical Storm Grace, which hit the same region late Monday, "is further disrupting access to water, shelter, and other basic services," UNICEF said.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5,000-10,000 Americans are still near Kabul, the Pentagon estimates CNN'.

node.text:
“We think there are certainly thousands of Americans. We don’t have an exact count. I would say somewhere best guess between 5 and 10,000 near Kabul,” Pentagon press secretary John Kirby said Tuesday. ⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio for the latest on Afghanistan.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WE SPOKE TO TEACHERS IN STATES WHERE MASK MANDATES ARE BANNED CNN'.

node.text:
We spoke with teachers in states where mask mandates are prohibited — including Texas, Florida, Oklahoma, Missouri, Arizona and Iowa. Some teachers feared for their students and others worried about bringing the virus home to their families. Swipe through to learn about their stories

They requested CNN withhold their last names out of fear of retribution.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WE SPOKE TO TEACHERS IN STATES WHERE MASK MANDATES ARE BANNED CNN'.

Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" I have no power. There are no teacher unions in Texas. Walking back into my school building is going to feel like I'm a lamb walking into a slaughterhouse. CNN Julie Houston'.

Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" My biggest concer this year is that there is a real possibility one of my fifth graders could die from Covid-19 and I can't do anything to protect them because it is against the law. CNN Pam• Oklahoma'.

Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" Gov. DeSantis said, "We need our kids to breathe." I immediately thought, "How can they breathe if they're dead?" I know that's so morbid and so dark, but that's the reality. Victoria CNN Palm Beach County, Florida'.

Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" We may not all agree politically, that's fine, but we all have a common enemy and that enemy is Covid. Why are we not unified on that? CNN Diane• Diane Jacksonville, Florida'.

Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, car, road and text that says 'There are almost no women on the streets of Kabul The Taliban have been in charge of Kabul for 48 hours. For terrified civilians, the dread is all-encompassing. CNN'.

node.text:
Since the Taliban took over Kabul, women have largely stayed indoors. Those who do brave the outside world tend to be dressed more conservatively than before, their faces often covered.⁠
⁠
One shopkeeper said his customers — largely men — are frightened and are buying burqas, which cover the body from head to toe, for their wives, daughters and other women in their lives. They feel that from now on, wearing a burqa may be the only way for them to stay safe on the streets.⁠
⁠
(📸: Hoshang Hashimi/AFP/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BREAKING NEWS The US is shipping the first of the 500 million Pfizer doses that President Biden pledged to donate around the world CNN'.

node.text: The US is sending 488,370 doses of the Covid-19 vaccine to Rwanda, a White House official told CNN on Tuesday. The move is part of President Biden's effort to have America be an "arsenal of vaccines" in the fight against Covid-19.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of mountain and text that says 'For the first time ever, a water shortage was declared on the Colorado River CNN'.

node.text:
The federal government on Monday declared a water shortage on the Colorado River for the first time, triggering mandatory water consumption cuts for states in the Southwest. Lake Mead, the Colorado River reservoir, is at its lowest since the lake was filled after the Hoover Dam was completed in the 1930s.⁠
⁠
(📸: Ethan Miller/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of airplane, outdoors and text.

node.text:
Now that the Taliban are in control of Kabul, Ismail is afraid to leave his house. Ismail — whose last name is being withheld to protect his safety — is one of scores of Afghans who worked alongside the US during its two-decade military campaign in Afghanistan and are now desperate for the US government's help in getting out of the country.⁠
⁠
(📸: Wakil Kohsar/AFP/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'BREAKING NEWS New Zealand announces it's locking down the entire country... over one Covid case CNN'.

node.text: New Zealand's Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern has announced a nationwide lockdown after the country confirmed one coronavirus case — the first locally transmitted Covid-19 case in the community since February. Everyone must stay home and businesses are closed aside for essential services such as supermarkets and pharmacies.⁠
